node.text: Video dedicated for my baby girl Wolfie, I hope you will enjoy watching it when you get older so you can remember & relive those amazing moments we had together (everytime i think of the fact babies forget when they’re babies as they grow it makes me cry cause I cannot believe those moments are soooo intense for me but she won’t remember🥺) hope this video will help hihi ❤️ As you can see, you were always the most intelligent, beautiful & incredible girl, you certainly still are today (yes talking to you Wolfie of the future haha) You make everyday the most beautiful day of my life again & again & again. You have this super power of bringing everyone together & making everyone smile on a daily basis 💕 i love you mi amor , the most loved baby on the planet 🍉

node.text: Made it to our first stop, we were supposed to stay in Costa Rica for a couple more weeks but I got a last minute news yesterday night & had to hop on a flight this morning ✈️ can you guess where we are going ? It’s a country starting with a C , it has snow & beautiful mountains… uhm 😏 i’ll update you tomorrow on my youtube channel with everything that happened & also everything that will happen for our future 🏡 ps: Wolfie seems sleepy & sweet but I swear she was a little monster in the plane but fell asleep for the last 10 minutes.. now we have a couple hours layover & she’s sleeping.. guess who will be a monster again in our next flight .. at least she’s a cute monster 🐒

node.text: Probably the product I am the proudest to have created in my entire life 🌸 i’m so proud to let you know that the breastfeeding bra is now available on @hoaka_apparel 🤱🏼 Hoaka is a brand not like any others, Hoaka is like “me”, i don’t really know how to explain it but usually brands have a specific branding & respect it, that’s simply how it works but I feel like for Hoaka it’s more than that .. i really create every products from my mood, how I feel, what I need, my brand is following my evolution and it’s growing up with me 🌸 when I started, I was 17, I was really young and was making a certain style of bikini, as I’m growing up, i like different things & when I launch new products on Hoaka I often get the “it doesn’t look like Hoaka” or “it’s so different from what you usually make” and i’m just like YESSSS 🥲 I still make & love what I’ve always done but I also grew up so much, it’s been 6 years already & so many things happened in my life since then.. i had the choice to keep every products “on brand” by keep making junior style swims OR just go with my vibe of the moment & create things for me.. that’s what I decided to do 🌈 Breastfeeding bras are what I needed but couldn’t find anything enough practical + comfy + nice looking .. so I created one for me & i’m happy to share it with you 🥰 I honestly have no idea if I have alot of breastfeeding mom here following me & loving Hoaka which is why we made small quantities today & only in black cause it’s just a test !! If I see a real interest I’ll make more colors & sizes 🤞🏽 briefly I’m saying that because I was scared to launch this product & loose the “young girls” vibe Hoaka always had but honestly, I grew up, the brand grew up & why couldn’t a “old eli” wear a “young girl” bikini or underwear right ?! I think i’m not so clear hahah sorry I wanted to let you know my thoughts so here they are the way I hear them in my head 😂💭

node.text:
At your best, you still won’t be good enough for the wrong person. At your worst, you’ll still be worth it for the right person ✨
I’ve read that quote so much in my life & always thought wow it’s so true but I would always think about someone else in my life, now I really just want to feel good enough for myself.. That’s not how I feel right now, I’m putting so much pressure on me & even at my best I’m still being difficult with myself. I’m working on it everyday, I’m trying to be able to just stop & be like “hey eli you did good, that was great” but I feel eternally insatisfied which can be good for certain things, cause it really helps me pushing myself more & more but at the same time it won’t let me appreciate what I have 🥺 I just want a good balance cause I think it’ll be best for Wolfie when she grows up, I’m realizing that I’m such a Sagittarius, I’m not that stable & I need to keep moving otherwise I’m suffocating, that’s what was happening when I was in Mexico, & then in Canada & now here.. I think I pointed out my problem now & I really want this to end positively : i’m really working on this, I want to find the good balance between having a home where Wolfie can have a stable life + traveling the world & moving alot because that’s what keeps me alive ❤️ on that note, I have a flight tomorrow to a secret destination, I can’t wait to post my update video when I get there because we really need to catch up I have so much to tell you 🌈

node.text: Sometimes I’m really wondering if this is what some people think happens when they comment “eat more” “eat a burger” “anorexique” “too skinny” .. do you really think it is going to change something in how I eat ? My video isn’t serious at all haha but the subject in the caption kinda is for me, every single day I’m dealing with this kind of comments & it didn’t start yesterday, i’ve been dealing with this all my life. With time, I learnt how to ignore the mean people, when people are clearly saying things just to hurt I really don’t take it too seriously BUT when I see people who really looks concerned & tell me things like “you don’t look healthy I’m just checking in” THAT is very hurtful. My body is my body, I was born skinny, I grew up skinny, I thought having a baby might change something but finally not that much, Idk what to say at this point. All I get from these comments is : “ok so my body looks sick ?” I just want to come here & remind you that it’s NEVER OK to comment on anyone’s body, no matter what you think of it. We are all born differently & we all have a different genetic. Plus, even if I had a health problem: telling me I look sick & my body is too skinny isn’t going to help so please : simply don’t 🥲 love you all tho , thank you for caring but I’m good, i even restarted training officially after pregnancy almost 2 months ago & i’m really proud of where I’m going 💪🏽 ps: bikini made out of recycled plastic from my braaand @hoaka_swimwear 👙♻️
